{"type":"message","id":"92cbb715","parentId":"3b8a57bc","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:43:40.751Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Discovering Bot Configuration**\n\nI'm zeroing in on how the bot's token is being handled. The absence of `src/config.py` is a key clue. My next step is examining `src/main.py` and `src/trading_bot.py`. I anticipate an environment variable is employed, and I'll search for \"TELEGRAM\" or \"TOKEN\" to confirm.\n\n\n**Inspecting the Loading Pattern**\n\nI've moved on to examining `src/main.py`. I want to understand the exact method used to load the bot's token. My initial hypothesis about environment variables seems likely, given the missing configuration file. However, I need to know *how* to access the token for independent script execution.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771159420749_745","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/main.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":6360,"output":162,"cacheRead":5066,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":6522,"cost":{"input":0.012719999999999999,"output":0.001944,"cacheRead":0.0010132000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0156772}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771159415785}}
{"type":"message","id":"24cfae44","parentId":"92cbb715","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:43:40.769Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771159420749_745","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import os\nimport sys\nimport subprocess\nimport logging\nimport asyncio\nfrom telegram import Update, BotCommand\nfrom telegram.ext import ApplicationBuilder, ContextTypes, CommandHandler\n\n# Configure logging\nlogging.basicConfig(\n    format='%(asctime)s - %(name)s - %(levelname)s - %(message)s',\n    level=logging.INFO\n)\n\n# Paths (Assuming run from workspace root)\nAGENT_WRAPPER = \"src/agent_wrapper.py\"\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nMASTER_PROTOCOL = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nEVOLUTION_LOG = \"docs_archive/EVOLUTION_LOG.md\"\n\n# Token from Env\nTOKEN = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n\nasync def dm_start(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🚀 Start DMarket HFT (High-Frequency)\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🚀 Starting DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        # Run agent_wrapper from root\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/start_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        # Format output\n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to start bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_stop(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"\"\"\n    await update.message.reply_text(\"🛑 Stopping DMarket HFT Bot...\")\n    try:\n        result = subprocess.run([sys.executable, AGENT_WRAPPER, \"/stop_bot\"], capture_output=True, text=True)\n        \n        output = result.stdout\n        if result.stderr:\n            output += \"\\nErrors:\\n\" + result.stderr\n            \n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"```\\n{output.strip()}\\n```\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n    except Exception as e:\n        await update.message.reply_text(f\"Failed to stop bot: {e}\")\n\nasync def dm_status(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"\"\"\n    status_msg = \"📊 **Bot Status Report**\\n\\n\"\n    \n    # 1. PID / Running State\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                pid = f.read().strip()\n            status_msg += f\"✅ **Status:** Active (PID: {pid})\\n\"\n        except:\n            status_msg += \"⚠️ **Status:** PID file error\\n\"\n    else:\n        status_msg += \"💤 **Status:** Inactive (No PID file)\\n\"\n\n    # 2. Master Protocol Version\n    version = \"Unknown\"\n    if os.path.exists(MASTER_PROTOCOL):\n        try:\n            with open(MASTER_PROTOCOL, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                # Look for Title or Version line\n                content = f.read()\n                lines = content.splitlines()\n                for line in lines:\n                    if \"Version\" in line or \"v.\" in line.lower():\n                        version = line.strip()\n                        break\n                if version == \"Unknown\" and lines:\n                     version = lines[0].strip()\n        except Exception as e:\n             version = f\"Error: {e}\"\n    status_msg += f\"📜 **Protocol:** {version}\\n\"\n\n    # 3. Evolution Log (Last Change)\n    last_change = \"None\"\n    if os.path.exists(EVOLUTION_LOG):\n        try:\n             with open(EVOLUTION_LOG, 'r', encoding='utf-8') as f:\n                lines = f.readlines()\n                # Get last non-empty line\n                for line in reversed(lines):\n                    if line.strip():\n                        last_change = line.strip()\n                        break\n        except:\n            pass\n    status_msg += f\"🧬 **Last Evolution:** {last_change}\\n\"\n    \n    # 4. LangFuse (Placeholder)\n    status_msg += \"🔎 **LangFuse Traces:** Active (Monitoring)\\n\"\n\n    await update.message.reply_text(status_msg, parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def dm_dashboard(update: Update, context: ContextTypes.DEFAULT_TYPE):\n    \"\"\"📈 Open Control Panel\"\"\"\n    # Assuming local streamlit or configured URL\n    url = os.getenv(\"STREAMLIT_URL\", \"http://localhost:8501\")\n    await update.message.reply_text(f\"📈 **Control Panel:** [Open Dashboard]({url})\", parse_mode='Markdown')\n\nasync def post_init(application):\n    \"\"\"Set up commands on bot startup\"\"\"\n    commands = [\n        BotCommand(\"dm_start\", \"🚀 Start DMarket HFT\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_stop\", \"🛑 EMERGENCY STOP & Flush\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_status\", \"📊 Bot Health & Balance\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_dashboard\", \"📈 Open Control Panel\"),\n    ]\n    await application.bot.set_my_commands(commands)\n    logging.info(\"Commands registered with Telegram.\")\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    if not TOKEN:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not set. Please set it in your environment.\")\n        # For testing purposes, we might want to exit gracefully or mock it, \n        # but for a real deployment, we exit.\n        sys.exit(1)\n        \n    application = ApplicationBuilder().token(TOKEN).post_init(post_init).build()\n    \n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_start', dm_start))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_stop', dm_stop))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_status', dm_status))\n    application.add_handler(CommandHandler('dm_dashboard', dm_dashboard))\n    \n    print(\"Telegram Bot Control Interface Started.\")\n    application.run_polling()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771159420767}}
{"type":"message","id":"a15f8fd8","parentId":"24cfae44","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:43:49.329Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Designing the Script's Structure**\n\nI'm starting the `src/menu_refresh.py` script. The plan is to initialize a bot and register some commands. After that, the script will simply terminate. I'll make sure it uses the same method for the bot token as the `src/main.py` file, utilizing `os.getenv()`.\n\n\n**Scripting the Initialization**\n\nI'm now implementing `src/menu_refresh.py`. I've decided on the structure: construct the `Application`, set commands using `bot.set_my_commands()` within an async function, and run it with `asyncio.run()`. I've verified that `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN` is loaded correctly, as I'm following the same `os.getenv()` pattern. The initialization script should now be simple and focused. I'll need to figure out how to add the needed dependencies.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"read_1771159429325_746","name":"read","arguments":{"file_path":"src/agent_wrapper.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":7997,"output":398,"cacheRead":5486,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8395,"cost":{"input":0.015993999999999998,"output":0.004776,"cacheRead":0.0010972,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.021867199999999996}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771159420770}}
{"type":"message","id":"501f3e1e","parentId":"a15f8fd8","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:43:49.348Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771159429325_746","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"import sys\nimport os\nimport subprocess\nimport argparse\nimport signal\nimport time\nimport threading\nimport json\n\nPID_FILE = \"src/bot.pid\"\nBOT_SCRIPT = \"src/trading_bot.py\"\nPROTOCOL_FILE = \"docs_archive/MASTER_PROTOCOL.md\"\nCONFIG_FILE = \"openclaw.json\"\n\nFLEET_GAMES = [\"CS2\", \"Rust\", \"TF2\"]\n\ndef load_config():\n    \"\"\"Load config from openclaw.json.\"\"\"\n    if os.path.exists(CONFIG_FILE):\n        try:\n            with open(CONFIG_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                return json.load(f)\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error loading config: {e}\")\n    return {}\n\ndef reload_protocol():\n    \"\"\"Reloads the master protocol configuration.\"\"\"\n    print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Hot Reload: Active\")\n    # In a real implementation, this would signal the bot process or reload config\n    # For now, we just log as requested.\n\ndef monitor_protocol():\n    \"\"\"Monitors the protocol file for changes.\"\"\"\n    if not os.path.exists(PROTOCOL_FILE):\n        return\n\n    last_mtime = os.path.getmtime(PROTOCOL_FILE)\n    print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Monitoring {PROTOCOL_FILE} for changes...\")\n\n    while True:\n        try:\n            current_mtime = os.path.getmtime(PROTOCOL_FILE)\n            if current_mtime != last_mtime:\n                last_mtime = current_mtime\n                reload_protocol()\n            time.sleep(1)\n        except OSError:\n            pass\n        except Exception as e:\n            print(f\"Error monitoring protocol: {e}\")\n            time.sleep(5)\n\ndef start_monitor_thread():\n    \"\"\"Starts the monitor in a background thread.\"\"\"\n    monitor_thread = threading.Thread(target=monitor_protocol, daemon=True)\n    monitor_thread.start()\n\ndef is_running(pid):\n    \"\"\"Check if a process with the given PID is running.\"\"\"\n    try:\n        # Windows-specific check could be added here, but signal 0 is widely supported for existence check\n        # On Windows, os.kill with 0 is not supported in older versions, but usually fine in modern Python.\n        # Alternative: use tasklist\n        if os.name == 'nt':\n            # Use tasklist to check if PID exists\n            # Use errors='ignore' to handle potential non-UTF-8 output from localized Windows shell\n            output = subprocess.check_output(f'tasklist /FI \"PID eq {pid}\"', shell=True).decode(errors='ignore')\n            return str(pid) in output\n        else:\n            os.kill(pid, 0)\n            return True\n    except (OSError, subprocess.CalledProcessError):\n        return False\n\ndef start_bot():\n    config = load_config()\n    fleet_mode = config.get(\"fleet_mode\", False)\n\n    if fleet_mode:\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Fleet Mode: ACTIVE\")\n        for game in FLEET_GAMES:\n            pid_file = f\"src/bot_{game.lower()}.pid\"\n            if os.path.exists(pid_file):\n                with open(pid_file, 'r') as f:\n                    try:\n                        pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                        if is_running(pid):\n                            print(f\"Worker for {game} already running (PID: {pid}).\")\n                            continue\n                        else:\n                            print(f\"Found stale PID file for {game}. Cleaning up.\")\n                            os.remove(pid_file)\n                    except ValueError:\n                        print(f\"Invalid PID file for {game}. Cleaning up.\")\n                        os.remove(pid_file)\n\n            print(f\"Spawning worker for {game}...\")\n            spawn_worker(game, pid_file)\n    else:\n        # Legacy single mode\n        if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                try:\n                    pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                    if is_running(pid):\n                        print(f\"Bot is already running (PID: {pid}).\")\n                        return\n                    else:\n                        print(\"Found stale PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n                except ValueError:\n                    print(\"Invalid PID file. Cleaning up.\")\n            \n            os.remove(PID_FILE)\n\n        print(\"Starting bot...\")\n        spawn_worker(None, PID_FILE)\n\ndef spawn_worker(game, pid_file):\n    args = [sys.executable, BOT_SCRIPT]\n    if game:\n        args.extend([\"--game\", game])\n    \n    # Detached execution\n    if os.name == 'nt':\n        # Windows: specific flags to detach\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            args,\n            creationflags=subprocess.CREATE_NEW_CONSOLE,\n            cwd=os.getcwd()\n        )\n    else:\n        # Unix\n        process = subprocess.Popen(\n            args,\n            stdout=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stderr=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            stdin=subprocess.DEVNULL,\n            cwd=os.getcwd(),\n            start_new_session=True\n        )\n\n    with open(pid_file, 'w') as f:\n        f.write(str(process.pid))\n    \n    label = game if game else \"Main\"\n    print(f\"Worker '{label}' started with PID: {process.pid}\")\n\ndef stop_bot():\n    config = load_config()\n    fleet_mode = config.get(\"fleet_mode\", False)\n    \n    pids_to_kill = []\n    \n    if fleet_mode:\n        for game in FLEET_GAMES:\n            pid_file = f\"src/bot_{game.lower()}.pid\"\n            if os.path.exists(pid_file):\n                pids_to_kill.append((game, pid_file))\n    \n    # Check main PID file too, just in case\n    if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n        pids_to_kill.append((\"Main\", PID_FILE))\n\n    if not pids_to_kill:\n        print(\"No active bots found.\")\n        return\n\n    for label, pid_file in pids_to_kill:\n        with open(pid_file, 'r') as f:\n            try:\n                pid = int(f.read().strip())\n            except ValueError:\n                print(f\"Invalid PID file for {label}.\")\n                os.remove(pid_file)\n                continue\n\n        if is_running(pid):\n            print(f\"Stopping {label} worker (PID: {pid})...\")\n            try:\n                if os.name == 'nt':\n                    subprocess.call(['taskkill', '/F', '/T', '/PID', str(pid)])\n                else:\n                    os.kill(pid, signal.SIGTERM)\n            except Exception as e:\n                print(f\"Error stopping {label}: {e}\")\n        else:\n            print(f\"{label} process not found. Cleaning up PID file.\")\n\n        if os.path.exists(pid_file):\n            os.remove(pid_file)\n    print(\"All bots stopped.\")\n\ndef status_bot():\n    config = load_config()\n    fleet_mode = config.get(\"fleet_mode\", False)\n    active_workers = 0\n    \n    if fleet_mode:\n        print(f\"FLEET MODE: ENABLED\")\n        for game in FLEET_GAMES:\n            pid_file = f\"src/bot_{game.lower()}.pid\"\n            status = \"INACTIVE\"\n            pid_info = \"\"\n            \n            if os.path.exists(pid_file):\n                with open(pid_file, 'r') as f:\n                    try:\n                        pid = int(f.read().strip())\n                        if is_running(pid):\n                            status = \"ACTIVE\"\n                            pid_info = f\"(PID: {pid})\"\n                            active_workers += 1\n                        else:\n                            status = \"STALE\"\n                    except:\n                        status = \"ERROR\"\n            \n            print(f\"  - {game}: {status} {pid_info}\")\n    else:\n        if os.path.exists(PID_FILE):\n            with open(PID_FILE, 'r') as f:\n                content = f.read().strip()\n                try:\n                    pid = int(content)\n                    if is_running(pid):\n                        print(f\"STATUS: ACTIVE (PID: {pid})\")\n                        active_workers = 1\n                        return\n                    else:\n                        print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE (Stale PID file found)\")\n                except Exception as e:\n                    print(f\"STATUS: ERROR (Corrupted PID file): {e}\")\n        else:\n            print(\"STATUS: INACTIVE\")\n    \n    print(f\"TOTAL ACTIVE WORKERS: {active_workers}\")\n\ndef main():\n    parser = argparse.ArgumentParser(description=\"Bot Control Interface\")\n    parser.add_argument('command', choices=['/start_bot', '/stop_bot', '/status', '/monitor'], help=\"Command to execute\")\n    \n    if len(sys.argv) < 2:\n        parser.print_help()\n        sys.exit(1)\n\n    args = parser.parse_args()\n\n    if args.command == '/start_bot':\n        start_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/stop_bot':\n        stop_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/status':\n        status_bot()\n    elif args.command == '/monitor':\n        print(f\"[{time.strftime('%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S')}] Starting protocol monitor...\")\n        monitor_protocol()\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    main()\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771159429346}}
{"type":"message","id":"fae6e8ce","parentId":"501f3e1e","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:44:03.765Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Defining the Approach**\n\nI'm now focusing on how the agent will \"search the web\". The user wants me, the agent, to perform the search directly, employing my own `web_search` tool and incorporating the results. I'm considering writing the results to a file or handling them internally within the script.\n\n\n**Deciphering the Requirements**\n\nI've been re-reading the prompt, specifically the \"simulated for now\" section. It's becoming clearer that the actual web searching isn't the immediate focus. The goal seems to be creating the `NewsWatcher` class and how it *interacts* with a search, which *simulates* a call to the web. I will create a basic class to handle the simulated web search, as an interim step.\n\n\n**Revisiting the Strategy**\n\nNow I am going back to the core challenge: the simulated web search, as the Python script has to \"run once\" and fetch \"1 real headline.\" I've decided to create the `NewsWatcher` class, which will fetch data from an RSS feed or webpage directly using `requests`. This bypasses the need for an API key. For testing, I'll use the CS2 updates RSS feed.  I will adapt to the user's need to simulate. I have already started `src/menu_refresh.py`.\n\n\n**Evaluating the Implementation**\n\nI'm now implementing the `NewsWatcher` class and considering how to integrate it with the telegram bot. I've successfully implemented `menu_refresh.py` to refresh Telegram bot commands. Now, I will implement `news_watcher.py` using `requests` to fetch headlines from the CS2 RSS feed. I will add a test to the script and call the script from the main program.\n\n\n**Examining Package Dependencies**\n\nI'm now checking the package dependencies for the project. I'll execute a `pip list` command to verify the presence of required libraries like `feedparser` and `python-telegram-bot`, among others. This will help determine the best approach for web data retrieval and ensure the program runs smoothly. Based on the existing `src/main.py` dependencies, I already know a few are there.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771159443761_747","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"pip list"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":10537,"output":1114,"cacheRead":5873,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":11651,"cost":{"input":0.021074,"output":0.013368,"cacheRead":0.0011746,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0356166}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771159429348}}
