{"type":"message","id":"0af70675","parentId":"42ce65da","timestamp":"2026-02-15T12:44:19.481Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Considering Package Availability**\n\nI've been assessing the available packages. I'll utilize `python-telegram-bot` and `requests` for the initial tasks. The absence of `feedparser` complicates parsing XML feeds. I'm leaning toward using `xml.etree.ElementTree` or possibly regex, keeping in mind the complexity of the feed. I'll need to install BeautifulSoup4, which will slow things down.\n\n\n**Defining Core Modules**\n\nI'm now focusing on module structure. I'll develop `src/menu_refresh.py`. I'll employ `requests` for fetching the RSS feed, and then use `xml.etree.ElementTree` to parse it. This simplifies dependencies. I'm prioritizing minimal external libraries for a cleaner implementation.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771159459475_748","name":"write","arguments":{"content":"import os\nimport asyncio\nfrom telegram import Bot, BotCommand, BotCommandScopeDefault\n\nasync def main():\n    token = os.getenv(\"TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN\")\n    if not token:\n        print(\"Error: TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN not set.\")\n        return\n\n    print(\"Initializing bot...\")\n    bot = Bot(token=token)\n    \n    commands = [\n        BotCommand(\"dm_start\", \"🚀 Start HFT Trading\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_stop\", \"🛑 STOP Trading\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_status\", \"📊 Fleet Status\"),\n        BotCommand(\"dm_dashboard\", \"📈 Dashboard\"),\n    ]\n    \n    print(\"Refreshing bot commands...\")\n    try:\n        await bot.set_my_commands(commands, scope=BotCommandScopeDefault())\n        print(\"Commands refreshed successfully.\")\n        \n        # Verify\n        current = await bot.get_my_commands()\n        print(\"Current commands:\")\n        for cmd in current:\n            print(f\" - /{cmd.command}: {cmd.description}\")\n            \n    except Exception as e:\n        print(f\"Error updating commands: {e}\")\n\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\n    asyncio.run(main())\n","file_path":"src/menu_refresh.py"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":14453,"output":493,"cacheRead":9354,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":14946,"cost":{"input":0.028905999999999998,"output":0.005916,"cacheRead":0.0018708000000000002,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0366928}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771159448841}}
